<section class="w-section">
  <div class="w-inner">
    <p class="w-eyebrow">The SDK</p>
    <h2 class="w-h2">One import. One schema.<br />Everything you need to&nbsp;trade.</h2>
    <p class="w-lead"><span style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">mostlyright</span> is a Python SDK and API. Install it, query whichever surface you need: market data, source data, settlement records. All in one schema, all temporally honest. Live endpoints return the same fields as historical archives. Every response carries a reproducibility token. Every record knows when it would have been&nbsp;knowable.</p>

    <div class="w-pillar-grid">
      <div class="w-pillar">
        <h3>Weather data</h3>
        <p>Hourly observations from three merged sources. Daily climate records — the actual settlement source for Kalshi temperature markets. Discrete model forecasts (NBS, NBE, GFS) and seamless ensemble series (HRRR, ECMWF). GOES-16/19 satellite at native cadence. Twenty US stations and growing&nbsp;internationally.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-pillar">
        <h3>Market data</h3>
        <p>Kalshi and Polymarket in one schema. Candles, events, series. Level-2 order book snapshots stored at native cadence. Resolution criteria attached to every market — your agent never has to ask what "high temperature" means for a given&nbsp;contract.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-pillar">
        <h3>Settlement-grade by default</h3>
        <p>Raw-as-reported storage. First observation wins. Corrections preserved separately so you choose what enters your training data. Source-priority dedup at storage. Float64 end-to-end. No silent rounding, no silent&nbsp;overwrites.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-pillar">
        <h3>Built for agents</h3>
        <p>TOON serialization saves up to 60% of your token budget vs JSON. Tool definitions export directly to Anthropic's tool-use format. Temporally-honest queries (snapshot, as_of) eliminate look-ahead bias by construction. Reproducibility tokens on every&nbsp;result.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
